  When it comes to writing a blog post, there are multiple formats you can use—and it all depends on the goal of your article and what your audience is looking for.
  
  Here are some popular types of blog posts to know, along with examples of how to use them:
  
  01. [How-to guides](https://ahrefs.com/blog/types-of-blog-posts/#1-how-to-guides)
  02. [Content hubs](https://ahrefs.com/blog/types-of-blog-posts/#2-content-hubs)
  03. [Expanded definition posts](https://ahrefs.com/blog/types-of-blog-posts/#3-expanded-definition-posts)
  04. [Listicles, aka list posts](https://ahrefs.com/blog/types-of-blog-posts/#4-listicles)
  05. [Expanded list posts](https://ahrefs.com/blog/types-of-blog-posts/#5-expanded-list-posts)
  06. [News](https://ahrefs.com/blog/types-of-blog-posts/#6-news)
  07. [Data studies](https://ahrefs.com/blog/types-of-blog-posts/#7-data-studies)
  08. [Case studies](https://ahrefs.com/blog/types-of-blog-posts/#8-case-studies)
  09. [Cheat sheets and checklists](https://ahrefs.com/blog/types-of-blog-posts/#9-cheat-sheets-and-checklists)
  10. [Templates](https://ahrefs.com/blog/types-of-blog-posts/#10-templates)
  
  ## 1\. How-to guides
  
  A how-to post offers a series of specific, chronological steps on how to achieve a goal. It’s typically structured like so:
  
  ![Infographic showing structure of a how-to guide, a common type of blog post format.](data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=%22http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%22%20viewBox=%220%200%20581%201120%22%3E%3C/svg%3E)
  
  For instance, [this post](https://ahrefs.com/blog/how-to-choose-keywords-for-seo/) is titled “How to Choose the Right Words for SEO” and shows you how to achieve that goal through a four-step process:
  
  - **Step 1** – Find keywords with search traffic potential
  - **Step 2** – Create content that aligns with search intent
  - **Step 3** – Ensure the keyword has “business potential”
  - **Step 4** – Make sure you can rank for the keyword
  
  We then elaborate on each step by showing you how to execute it.
  
  In the case of **step one**—finding keywords with search traffic potential—we suggested using keyword research tools such as [Google Keyword Planner](https://ahrefs.com/blog/google-keyword-planner/) and Ahrefs’ [Keywords Explorer](https://app.ahrefs.com/keywords-explorer) and then elaborated on how each tool works.
  
  ![Excerpt of an Ahrefs article talking about GKP and Ahrefs' Keywords Explorer ](data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=%22http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%22%20viewBox=%220%200%20210%20140%22%3E%3C/svg%3E)
  
  ### Best practices
  
  - When chronicling your steps in a how-to type of blog post, be as specific as possible. Consider that your reader may ask, “How? Why?” and then fill these gaps to make your how-to guide substantial.
  
