  ## 1\. Blog posts
  
  Blog posts are a great way to educate your audience and “sell” what you do in the process.
  
  ### Example
  
  Our [list of free keyword research tools](https://ahrefs.com/blog/free-keyword-research-tools/) features four of our own tools.
  ![Ahrefs' post on free keyword research tools ](https://ahrefs.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/image15-3.png)
  
  ### How to market them
  
  If you want consistent traffic to your blog posts, write about topics people search for on Google and [use SEO to rank high](https://ahrefs.com/blog/how-to-rank-higher-on-google/).
  
  How can you find these topics?
  
  Look at which of your competitors’ posts get the most organic search traffic.
  
  Here’s how:
  
  1. Go to Ahrefs’ [Site Explorer](https://ahrefs.com/site-explorer)
  2. Enter a popular industry blog
  3. Go to the **Top pages** report
  4. Toggle **SERP titles** on
  
  ![Top pages report, via Ahrefs' Site Explorer ](data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=%22http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%22%20viewBox=%220%200%201108%20962%22%3E%3C/svg%3E)
  
  Further reading
  
  - [How to Write a Blog Post (That People Actually Want to Read) in 9 Steps](https://ahrefs.com/blog/how-to-write-a-blog-post/)
  
  ## 2\. Videos
  
  Videos are a great way to reach a wide audience and show your product or service in action.
  
  ### Example
  
  Our video on lesser-known link building tactics shows how you can execute them with the help of our toolset.
  
  Link Building Tactics No One is Talking About - YouTube
  
  Tap to unmute
  
  [Link Building Tactics No One is Talking About](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=B5jmQig8FJU) [Ahrefs](https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/channel/UCWquNQV8Y0_defMKnGKrFOQ)
  
  Ahrefs667K subscribers
  
  [Watch on](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=B5jmQig8FJU)
  
  ### How to market them
  
  If you’re starting out with no audience, the best way to generate traffic to your videos is to rank high on YouTube. You can do this by targeting topics people are searching for on YouTube.
  
  Here’s how to find these topics:
  
  1. Go to Ahrefs’ [Keywords Explorer](https://ahrefs.com/keywords-explorer)
  2. Switch the tab to **YouTube**
  3. Enter one or a few relevant keywords
  4. Go to the **Matching terms** report
  
  ![Finding "YouTube" keywords, via Ahrefs' Keywords Explorer](data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=%22http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%22%20viewBox=%220%200%201694%201110%22%3E%3C/svg%3E)
  
  Further reading
  
  - [YouTube SEO: How to Rank Your Videos From Start to Finish](https://ahrefs.com/blog/youtube-seo/)
  
  ## 3\. Podcasts
  
  Podcasts are a great way to build brand awareness, reach a wide audience, and network with industry experts.
  
  ### Example
  
  In only six months, HubSpot’s “Marketing Against the Grain” podcast hit [70,000 monthly downloads](https://www.linkedin.com/posts/kieranjflanagan_we-grew-marketing-against-the-grain-to-activity-6981237691187134464-5pi5/?originalSubdomain=sn)—many of whom are marketers and potential customers.
  [![](data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=%22http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%22%20viewBox=%220%200%201111%20596%22%3E%3C/svg%3E)](https://open.spotify.com/show/3bMqKPfI45OmTK5hENtIOk) [Listen to Marketing Against the Grain on Spotify](https://open.spotify.com/show/3bMqKPfI45OmTK5hENtIOk)
  
  ### How to market them
  
  A few ideas to get the word out for your podcast:
  
  - Record your podcast as a video so it can be uploaded on YouTube (instead of just having it in audio)
  - Share snippets of your podcast on social media ( [here’s an example](https://twitter.com/ramit/status/1643327598389346313))
  - Be a guest on other podcasts
  - Transcribe your podcast and [send highlights to journalists](https://tim.blog/2016/04/11/tim-ferriss-podcast-business/)
  
  ## 4\. How-tos
  
  How-tos are a great way to teach your audience to solve problems step by step with your product or service.
  
  ### Example
  
  Our [article on keyword optimization](https://ahrefs.com/blog/keyword-optimization/) shows how to complete the process with our toolset.
  ![Ahrefs' blog post on keyword optimization ](data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=%22http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%22%20viewBox=%220%200%201274%201350%22%3E%3C/svg%3E)
  
  ### How to market them
  
  The best way is to rank your how-tos on Google and generate consistent search traffic. To do this, target “how to” keywords.
  
  Here’s how to find them:
  
  1. Go to Ahrefs’ [Keywords Explorer](https://ahrefs.com/keywords-explorer)
  2. Enter one or a few relevant keywords
  3. Go to the **Matching terms** report
  4. In the **Include** filter, add “how”
  
  ![Finding "how to" keywords, via Ahrefs' Keywords Explorer ](data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=%22http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%22%20viewBox=%220%200%201560%201406%22%3E%3C/svg%3E)
  
  ## 5\. Guides
  
  Guides are a great way to introduce your audience to a specific topic and insert your product or service in the process.
  
  ### Example
  
  Our [beginner’s guide to technical SEO](https://ahrefs.com/seo/technical-seo) explains everything you need to know about technical SEO, including how to use our toolset to fix technical issues.
  ![Ahrefs' guide to technical SEO ](data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=%22http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%22%20viewBox=%220%200%201644%201680%22%3E%3C/svg%3E)
  
  ### How to market them
  
  The best way is to rank your guides high on Google. Here’s how to find guide-related topics:
  
  1. Go to Ahrefs’ [Keywords Explorer](https://ahrefs.com/keywords-explorer)
  2. Enter one or a few relevant keywords
  3. Go to the **Matching terms** report
  4. In the **Include** filter, add “what”
  
  ![Finding "guide" keywords, via Ahrefs' Keywords Explorer ](data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=%22http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%22%20viewBox=%220%200%201188%201468%22%3E%3C/svg%3E)
  
  Sidenote.
  
  Not all of this will be guide-related keywords (e.g., “what does seo stand for”), so make sure you analyze the SERPs first.
  
  ## 6\. Newsletters
  
  Newsletters are a great way to build an audience whom you can reach out to any time. They’re also great for [distributing content](https://ahrefs.com/blog/content-distribution/).
  
  ### Example
  
  We send a [weekly newsletter](https://ahrefs.com/newsletter) to 200,000 people that features content from our blog and elsewhere.
  ![Example of an Ahrefs' Digest issue ](data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=%22http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%22%20viewBox=%220%200%201158%201458%22%3E%3C/svg%3E)
  
  ### How to market them
  
  The best way is to encourage people to opt in for the newsletter when they’re already consuming your content. You can do this via a simple opt-in (like us) or with an incentive (via the other content formats in this post).
  ![Ahrefs' subscribe box ](data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=%22http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%22%20viewBox=%220%200%20522%20396%22%3E%3C/svg%3E)
  
  Further reading
  
  - [8 Easy (But Effective) Ways to Grow Your Email List](https://ahrefs.com/blog/grow-email-list/)
  
  ## 7\. Listicles
  
  Don’t just riff off a list of items; expand your listicles with specific steps. This will allow you to “sell” your product or service naturally.
  
  ### Example
  
  Our [listicle on driving traffic to your website](https://ahrefs.com/blog/how-to-drive-traffic-to-your-website/) shows how you can use our toolset in different tactics.
  ![Ahrefs' blog post on driving traffic to your website ](data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=%22http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%22%20viewBox=%220%200%201676%201448%22%3E%3C/svg%3E)
  Another common type of listicle: product review and comparison articles, like this [list of best marketing platforms](https://waltervoronovic.com/business-software-reviews/best-all-in-one-marketing-platforms/).
  ![](data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=%22http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%22%20viewBox=%220%200%201950%201418%22%3E%3C/svg%3E)
  
  ### How to market them
  
  Like other blog post formats, the best way is to rank your listicle high on Google. Here’s how to find potential list-based topics:
  
  1. Go to Ahrefs’ [Keywords Explorer](https://ahrefs.com/keywords-explorer)
  2. Enter one or a few relevant keywords
  3. Go to the **Matching terms** report
  4. In the **Include** filter, add list-based keywords like “ideas, tips, tools, things, strategies, tactics, list”
  
  ![Finding "listicle" keywords, via Ahrefs' Keywords Explorer ](data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=%22http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%22%20viewBox=%220%200%201496%201584%22%3E%3C/svg%3E)
  
  Further reading
  
  - [How to Write a Great Listicle Post in 10 Steps](https://ahrefs.com/blog/listicle/)
  
  ## 8\. Ebooks
  
  Usually <100 pages, ebooks work as great incentives to encourage visitors to opt in to your email list.
  
  ### Example
  
  To get a free copy of Intercom’s [book on marketing](https://www.intercom.com/resources/books/intercom-marketing), it requires prospects to fill in relevant details (e.g., name, email address, and more).
  ![Intercom's opt-in box for its book ](data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=%22http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%22%20viewBox=%220%200%20906%201736%22%3E%3C/svg%3E)
  
  ### How to market them
  
  Create a dedicated landing page for your ebook that’s designed to capture email addresses. You can then link to this landing page from your blog posts or run ads to it.
  
  ## 9\. Physical books
  
  Physical books are generally regarded as high-value and signal that the brand is serious about content and education.
  
  ### Example
  
  The [launch of our new SEO book for beginners](https://ahrefs.com/blog/seo-for-beginners-book/) generated a positive reception.
  
  https://twitter.com/r\_betelgeuse/status/1649409619951845378
  
  ### How to market them
  
  The best way to market a book is [word of mouth](https://ahrefs.com/blog/word-of-mouth-marketing/). To get the flywheel going, run a giveaway of your book.
  
  https://twitter.com/ahrefs/status/1645849220149309446
  
  ## 10\. Checklists
  
  Checklists are a great way to drive tons of search traffic and insert your product or service as part of the checklist. They can also work well as a content upgrade.
  
  ### Example
  
  Our [SEO checklist](https://ahrefs.com/blog/seo-checklist/) ranks in position #2 and generates a lot of search traffic.
  ![Ahrefs' SEO checklist post ranks in position #2, via Ahrefs' Keywords Explorer ](data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=%22http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%22%20viewBox=%220%200%201626%20662%22%3E%3C/svg%3E)
  
  ### How to market them
  
  The best way is to rank your checklist high on Google. Here’s how to find potential checklist topics:
  
  1. Go to Ahrefs’ [Keywords Explorer](https://ahrefs.com/keywords-explorer)
  2. Enter one or a few relevant keywords
  3. Go to the **Matching terms** report
  4. In the **Include** filter, add “checklist”
  
  ![Finding "checklist" keywords, via Ahrefs' Keywords Explorer ](data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=%22http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%22%20viewBox=%220%200%201310%201472%22%3E%3C/svg%3E)
  
  ## 11\. Templates
  
  Like checklists, templates are a good way to “insert” your product or service into the process. They also work well as [lead magnets](https://ahrefs.com/blog/lead-magnet/).
  
  ### Example
  
  Our [guide to keyword strategy](https://ahrefs.com/blog/keyword-strategy/) offers a free template for anyone to copy.
  ![Ahrefs' guide to keyword strategy ](data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=%22http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%22%20viewBox=%220%200%201028%20440%22%3E%3C/svg%3E)
  
  ### How to market them
  
  Don’t create templates no one wants. Make sure people are looking for it. You can do this by looking for templates people are searching for.
  
  1. Go to Ahrefs’ [Keywords Explorer](https://ahrefs.com/keywords-explorer)
  2. Enter one or a few relevant keywords
  3. Go to the **Matching terms** report
  4. In the **Include** filter, add “template”
  
  ![Finding "template" keywords, via Ahrefs' Keywords Explorer ](data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=%22http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%22%20viewBox=%220%200%201216%201440%22%3E%3C/svg%3E)
  
  ## 12\. White papers
  
  Since the goal of a white paper is to show necessary data and facts to explain why a product is the best on the market, it can work as a lead magnet for prospects who are interested in learning more about your product.
  
  ### Example
  
  Ultimaker, a 3D printer manufacturer, gathers contact information from an audience interested in the real cost of owning a 3D printer.
  ![3D printing white paper from Ultimaker ](data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=%22http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%22%20viewBox=%220%200%201600%201225%22%3E%3C/svg%3E)
  
  ### How to market them
  
  Create a dedicated landing page for your white paper. You can then link to this landing page from your blog posts or run ads to it.
  
  ## 13\. Social media posts
  
  Social media posts are great for increasing brand awareness, reaching a broader audience, and building a following interested in your brand, content, product, or service.
  
  ### Example
  
  Ahrefs posts regularly on Twitter, including threads.
  
  https://twitter.com/ahrefs/status/1645456632439267328
  
  ### How to market them
  
  Each social media platform has its own rules, culture, and media type (e.g., short-form videos on TikTok, carousels on LinkedIn, long-form on Twitter). Learn what they are and create content that matches what people on the platform want to see.
  
  ## 14\. Illustrations and infographics
  
  Illustrations and infographics are great ways to condense text, concepts, and ideas into a shareable form. They also work great on social media.
  
  ### Example
  
  Our [post on how to get on the first page of Google](https://ahrefs.com/blog/how-to-get-on-the-first-page-of-google/) features a flowchart.
  ![Flowchart on how to get on the first page of Google ](data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=%22http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%22%20viewBox=%220%200%20913%201999%22%3E%3C/svg%3E)
  
  ### How to market them
  
  Create illustrations and infographics that people want to see. You can do this by following the TRUST formula:
  
  1. Find a **T** rending topic
  2. Do **R** esearch and analysis to find interesting data
  3. Present a **U** nique takeaway
  4. Create a **S** imple visual
  5. Promote **T** actically
  
  Further reading
  
  - [How to Get High-Quality Backlinks With the TRUST Formula \[Case Study\]](https://ahrefs.com/blog/the-trust-formula/)
  
  ## 15\. Tools
  
  Free tools are a great way to let customers test-drive your product or service.
  
  ### Example
  
  Our [backlink checker](https://ahrefs.com/backlink-checker) is one of the many [free SEO tools](https://ahrefs.com/free-seo-tools) we offer.
  ![Ahrefs' free backlink checker ](data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=%22http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%22%20viewBox=%220%200%201350%20922%22%3E%3C/svg%3E)
  
  ### How to market them
  
  Don’t guess what tools people want. Create them based on what people are searching for:
  
  1. Go to Ahrefs’ [Keywords Explorer](https://ahrefs.com/keywords-explorer)
  2. Enter one or a few relevant keywords
  3. Go to the **Matching terms** report
  4. In the **Include** filter, add “tool, tools, checker, calculator”
  
  ![Finding "tool" keywords, via Ahrefs' Keywords Explorer ](data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=%22http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%22%20viewBox=%220%200%201140%201256%22%3E%3C/svg%3E)
  
  ## 16\. Courses
  
  Courses are a great way to educate your audience, especially about how to use your product or use your product to solve their problems.
  
  ### Example
  
  Our [SEO course for beginners](https://ahrefs.com/academy/seo-training-course) teaches the basics of SEO using Ahrefs.
  ![Ahrefs' SEO course for beginners ](data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=%22http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%22%20viewBox=%220%200%201160%201446%22%3E%3C/svg%3E)
  
  ### How to market them
  
  Similarly, you’ll want to create courses for topics that people are searching for:
  
  1. Go to Ahrefs’ [Keywords Explorer](https://ahrefs.com/keywords-explorer)
  2. Enter one or a few relevant keywords
  3. Go to the **Matching terms** report
  4. In the **Include** filter, add “course”
  
  ![Finding "course" keywords, via Ahrefs' Keywords Explorer](data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=%22http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%22%20viewBox=%220%200%201108%201368%22%3E%3C/svg%3E)
  
  ## 17\. Case studies
  
  Case studies can be an effective nudge for turning a prospect into a customer.
  
  ### Example
  
  Recruiting software Lever has [hundreds of case studies](https://www.lever.co/customers/) based on customer size and industry.
  ![Lever's customer case studies ](data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=%22http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%22%20viewBox=%220%200%201390%201128%22%3E%3C/svg%3E)
  
  ### How to market them
  
  The best way is to add them to your website so visitors can navigate there.
  ![Lever's navigation to its case studies ](data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=%22http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%22%20viewBox=%220%200%201134%20452%22%3E%3C/svg%3E)
  They can also be used as part of your sales process.
  
  ## 18\. Testimonials
  
  Testimonials are a great way to add social proof to your website.
  
  ### Example
  
  We have a rolling carousel of testimonials on our homepage, separated by our customer profiles.
  ![Testimonials from happy Ahrefs customers ](data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=%22http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%22%20viewBox=%220%200%201182%201102%22%3E%3C/svg%3E)
  
  ### How to market them
  
  The best way is to put them on your homepage.
  
  ## 19\. Webinars
  
  Webinars are a great way to generate leads or onboard customers.
  
  ### Example
  
  We mainly use [webinars](https://community.ahrefs.com/c/events/) as onboarding at Ahrefs.
  ![The email that Ahrefs sends to invite people to the onboarding webinar ](data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=%22http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%22%20viewBox=%220%200%20730%20852%22%3E%3C/svg%3E)
  
  ### How to market them
  
  The specific promotion strategy will depend on your goals for webinars:
  
  - If you’re using them as onboarding for new or existing customers, you can promote them via your email list.
  - If you’re using them for [lead generation](https://ahrefs.com/blog/lead-generation/), consider partnering with experts and influencers in your niche so they can promote them to various audiences.
  
  Further reading
  
  - [How ConvertKit Grew From $98K to $625K MRR by Doing 150 Webinars in 1 Year](https://www.leadfeeder.com/blog/webinar-marketing/)
  
  ## 20\. Quizzes
  
  Quizzes are a great way to [acquire links](https://ahrefs.com/seo/link-building), build brand awareness, and segment your audience.
  
  ### Example
  
  Todoist runs a [quiz on the best productivity methods](https://todoist.com/productivity-methods).
  ![Todoist's productivity methods quiz ](data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=%22http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%22%20viewBox=%220%200%20932%20580%22%3E%3C/svg%3E)
  
  ### How to market them
  
  Add them to your website so visitors can navigate and find them.
  ![Todoist's navigation to its productivity methods quiz ](data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=%22http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%22%20viewBox=%220%200%201544%201136%22%3E%3C/svg%3E)
  
  ## 21\. Interactive content
  
  Interactive forms of content, like games, allow prospects and customers to play with content. They’re a great [type of content to attract backlinks](https://ahrefs.com/blog/link-bait/).
  
  ### Example
  
  Swedish financial company Advisa created a [game](https://advisa.se/en/research/brexit-bus/) to indirectly comment on the British pound after Brexit was confirmed.
  ![Brexit bus game ](data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=%22http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%22%20viewBox=%220%200%20958%20866%22%3E%3C/svg%3E)
  
  ### How to market them
  
  The best way is to pitch your interactive content to relevant news websites.
  
  Further reading
  
  - [Digital PR: The Beginner’s Guide to Making Your Brand Unmissable](https://ahrefs.com/blog/digital-pr/)
  - [9 Great Public Relations Tactics With Campaign Examples](https://ahrefs.com/blog/pr-tactics-examples/)
  
  ## 22\. Interviews
  
  Interviews are a great way to create expert content and tap into other people’s audiences. They can be in any format: video, audio, or text.
  
  ### Example
  
  Our chief marketing officer, [Tim Soulo](https://twitter.com/timsoulo?lang=en), interviews expert SEOs and marketers for our [customers-only community](https://community.ahrefs.com/):
  ![Ahrefs' interview series, "This Never Happened" ](data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=%22http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%22%20viewBox=%220%200%201198%201146%22%3E%3C/svg%3E)
  
  ### How to market them
  
  Promote your interview via your email list. You should also encourage your guest to promote the interview to their audience.
  
  ## 23\. Slide decks
  
  Slide decks are usually created for conferences and work well as thought leadership.
  
  ### Example
  
  This is a presentation from Tim at BrightonSEO, an SEO conference.
  
  https://www.slideshare.net/ahrefs/brightonseo-keyword-research
  
  ### How to market them
  
  After your presentation, upload your slide decks on SlideShare.
  
  ## 24\. Memes
  
  Primarily for social media, memes are a great way to engage with your audience.
  
  ### Example
  
  Fast-food restaurant Wendy’s is well known for posting memes on Twitter.
  
  > [pic.twitter.com/mZzgtv9uEi](https://t.co/mZzgtv9uEi)
  >
  > — Wendy’s (@Wendys) [September 14, 2022](https://twitter.com/Wendys/status/1570174502453084160?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw)
  
  ### How to market them
  
  Since memes are mainly for engaging with your audience, the best way is to post them on the social media platform you’re using to engage with said audience.
  
  ## 25\. User-generated content
  
  User-generated content (UGC) is a great way to build and engage with your audience.
  
  ### Example
  
  Every post and reply in our customers-only community is UGC and contributes to its engagement and activity.
  ![Posts and comments from members in Ahrefs' community ](data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=%22http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%22%20viewBox=%220%200%201242%201352%22%3E%3C/svg%3E)
  
  ### How to market them
  
  Rather than market UGC, a better way would be to figure out how to generate more of it. For example, we’d want more activity in our community (and therefore more UGC).
  
  While there’s no surefire way to do this, one thing’s certain—you have to be a brand that your customers love. That means creating an amazing product and providing great customer service.
  
  Beyond that, you’ll also want to make things exclusive so your customers feel like they’re part of an invite-only community. For example:
  
  - Our interview series, “This Never Happened,” is live, and the recording is only available to our community for 24 hours.
  - Adidas Yeezys are limited edition, and you can’t get them anywhere else.
  - To launch his chocolate brand, Feastables, MrBeast [embedded 10 golden tickets](https://tclarkmedia.substack.com/p/-how-mrbeast-launched-feastables) that represent the opportunity to be featured in a MrBeast video, remaking Willy Wonka’s Chocolate Factory in real life.
  
